
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Louvre Museum Exhibition Management System

class Location {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -description: String
}

class Exhibition {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
  -status: String
  -coordinator: Employee
}

class Employee {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -role: String
  -coach: Employee
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  -id: int
  -itemType: String
  -description: String
}

class Piece {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -artist: String
  -collector: Collector
}

class Collector {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -contactInfo: String
}

class RequestedPiece {
  -id: int
  -exhibitionItem: ExhibitionItem
  -piece: Piece
  -status: String
}

' Relationships

Location "1" --> "0..*" Exhibition : contains
Exhibition "1" --> "1" Employee : coordinator
Employee "0..1" --> "1" Employee : coach
Exhibition "1" --> "0..*" ExhibitionItem : has
ExhibitionItem "1" --> "0..*" RequestedPiece : requestedPieces
RequestedPiece "1" --> "1" Piece : provides
Piece "1" --> "1" Collector : belongsTo
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Location`**: Represents parts of the museum (e.g., wings, floors) where exhibitions are held.
- **`Exhibition`**: Contains details about each exhibition, including its coordinator.
- **`Employee`**: Each employee can be assigned as a coordinator or coach; junior employees have a senior coach.
- **`ExhibitionItem`**: Defines what items are needed for an exhibition (e.g., "a sunflower painting").
- **`Piece`**: Represents a specific artwork that may be sourced from a collector.
- **`Collector`**: Holds information about external collectors who own potential pieces.
- **`RequestedPiece`**: Tracks which piece is being requested for a particular exhibition item.

